  "prompt": "Which are the best airplane seats in economy class?",
  "response": "Choosing the best airplane seats in economy class often depends on personal preferences and the specific aircraft layout. However, some general tips can help you find more comfortable seats:\n\n1. **Exit Row Seats:** These seats usually offer extra legroom as they are located near emergency exits. However, be aware that some exit row seats do not recline.\n\n2. **Bulkhead Seats:** These seats are located directly behind partitions (bulkheads) which can provide more legroom. However, you may not have under-seat storage and some bulkhead seats may have slightly narrower widths due to tray tables located in the armrests.\n\n3. **Window Seats:** Ideal for passengers who want to lean against the wall and enjoy the view. These seats can be quieter and have less disturbance from people walking in the aisle.\n\n4. **Aisle Seats:** Good for ease of access to the aisle and restroom. Ideal for passengers who prefer more freedom to move around or need frequent access.\n\n5. **Seats Near the Front:** Located closer to the front of the cabin, these seats can reduce the amount of time waiting to exit the plane upon arrival and sometimes receive quicker meal service.\n\n6. **Seats with less noise:** Avoid seats near the galley and lavatories, as these areas tend to be more crowded and noisy.\n\nChecking seat maps and reviews on websites like SeatGuru or consulting the airline\u2019s seating chart can help you make a more informed decision. Remember that preferences and comfort can vary, so it's best to consider what's most important to you during a flight.",
